<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-02-16T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-02-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="643" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d643">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/218: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-02-16T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February 16,
                                        1922—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>36. Your 43, February 10, 11 a.m.</p>
                        <p>The Department understands that the Federal Company is proceeding under
                            its concession. The president of the Federal Company is <hi rend="italic">en route</hi> from New York to San Francisco but will
                            be communicated with as soon as possible. Meanwhile, you may if you so
                            deem necessary intimate to Chinese Minister of Communications that any
                            effort to discredit Federal should not be tolerated.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
